00:37:26.510 --> 00:37:28.080
&gt;&gt; Your mission in
the ionosphere,

00:37:28.080 --> 00:37:32.870
it appeared there were two
winds, potentially funny.

00:37:32.870 --> 00:37:35.590
Have they shown any
indication of some type

00:37:35.590 --> 00:37:37.640
of whirlpool configuration
that we see

00:37:37.640 --> 00:37:40.490
in rivers occurring
in the ionosphere?

00:37:40.490 --> 00:37:41.790
&gt;&gt; Sarah Jones: So
the question was

00:37:41.790 --> 00:37:43.670
about the two different
winds that are happening

00:37:43.670 --> 00:37:46.450
in the upper atmosphere, the
ion wind and the neutral wind,

00:37:46.450 --> 00:37:51.310
and whether or not we see
whirlpool type effects.

00:37:51.310 --> 00:37:54.430
Actually, there are all kinds
of really interesting effects,

00:37:54.430 --> 00:37:56.500
not exactly the same,
but happening

00:37:56.500 --> 00:37:58.170
in the upper atmosphere.

00:37:58.170 --> 00:38:02.830
For example, those two arms of
the mouse, the bands that are

00:38:02.830 --> 00:38:05.770
around the Earth,
they're really symmetrical

00:38:05.770 --> 00:38:09.210
around the Earth's
magnetic equator,

00:38:09.210 --> 00:38:14.270
and they actually are caused by
what's called a fountain effect,

00:38:14.270 --> 00:38:16.570
which occurs because
of the Earth's magnetic

00:38:16.570 --> 00:38:20.630
and electric fields pulling on
those ions, and it causes them

00:38:20.630 --> 00:38:24.310
to move upward and
then outward and down,

00:38:24.310 --> 00:38:26.010
kind of like a fountain,

00:38:26.010 --> 00:38:29.500
and that's what produces the
light in those two bands.

00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:33.320
There are also other patterns
that I'm not very familiar with,

00:38:33.320 --> 00:38:37.990
but one called the winter polar
vortex, which also moves air

00:38:37.990 --> 00:38:41.200
from the polar regions
down toward the equator.

00:38:41.200 --> 00:38:44.500
So yeah, there are a lot of
similarities like the two.

00:38:45.690 --> 00:38:48.920
&gt;&gt; What are the effects
of the El Nino thickening

00:38:48.920 --> 00:38:51.390
of the ionosphere on Earth?

00:38:51.390 --> 00:38:54.480
&gt;&gt; Sarah Jones: So the
thickening of the ionosphere,

00:38:54.480 --> 00:38:59.490
it could potentially cause
